#### 3 Introduction

IPEmotion YouTube channel:  http://www.youtube.com/user/IPEmotion/videos

growing number of video tutorials about the software and many different PlugIns.

#### 3.1 The next-generation data acquisition software

IPEmotion software takes a unique approach. Most DAQ software programs are designed to
support only one manufacturer's data acquisition hardware. However, IPEmotion is designed to
be a hardware-independent software that is not tied to any specific data acquisition hardware. In
fact, the software is based on open interfaces so that any hardware manufacturer can connect
its hardware to this software. IPETRONIK data acquisition modules and data loggers are integ-
rated into IPEmotion using the same plug-in interface standard as any other hardware system.
With IPEmotion, you can cover the entire data acquisition process, from configuring your data
sources/instruments, to displaying live data on different instruments and mimics, to automating
your test bench applications, to analyzing your stored data and generating a report output.

#### 3.2 The key features of IPEmotion

IPEmotion Software Overview:  https://youtu.be/aU4GL-NnZjs

3.2.1 Vendor independent PlugIn concept

Anyone can connect their hardware to IPEmotion by developing a plug-in. Documentation,
development tools and support are provided by IPETRONIK. Many hardware systems are
already supported and the list of supported hardware is constantly growing. The PlugIns are usu-
ally developed by the hardware manufacturers. More than 30 PlugIns are currently listed on the
IPEmotion website. If the hardware you want to use is not listed on the IPETRONIK website,
please contact the IPEmotion support team (support@ipetronik.com) to send your request and
we will check availability.

3.2.2 Configuration

IPEmotion's graphical user interface is uniquely designed to make it easy to do what every test
and measurement engineer does best - measure data. The entire user interface is based on con-
figuration dialogs. No programming is required to bring data onto the scree

3.2.3 COM interface for open programming

However, IPEmotion can also be seen as a development system for all customers who want to
solve complex DAQ and test bench applications. The COM and VBS/Python scripting interfaces
are a very efficient way of integrating specific functions into the program. Details on plug-in
development are available on the IPETRONIK website www.ipetronik.com.

3.2.4 Data API to access IPEmotion IAD data files 64 bit

An API is available for developers to write IPEmotion (.IAD) import filters for other programs.
This API was originally developed for importing (.IAD) files into NI DIAdem software. The Data
API is published on the IPETRONIK website at the following link:  www.ipetronik.com .

If you need to import IPEmotion (.IAD) files for National Instruments software applications, see
the following link:  http://search.n-
i.com/nisearch/app/main/p/bot/no/ap/tech/lang/de/pg/1/sn/ssnav:dpl/q/ipemotion/

3.2.5 OEM and customer-specific setups

IPEmotion is the only product of its kind in the world that allows customers to create their own
customised setup.

IPEmotion is based on technology that makes it easy to tailor and customize the software to
meet customer needs. Compared to most off-the-shelf data acquisition software packages, the
IPEmotion setup package can be perfectly tailored to company standards to increase pro-
ductivity in test and measurement labs.
